<法規內容>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 1</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[This Standard is prescribed in accordance with the provisions of Article 17 of the Act Governing Food Safety and Sanitation.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 2</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[Maximum tolerance of Lead in edible plant origin shall meet the following Table. (Wet weight basis except crops harvested solely for dry crop)
┌───────────┬─────┬────────────┐
│            ＼  Metals│  Lead    │      Applies scope     │
│Food Category ＼      │          │                        │
├───────────┼─────┼────────────┤
│                      │          │The maximum tolerance   │
│Leafy vegetables      │0.3ppm │also applies to Brassica│
│                      │          │leafy vegetables.       │
├───────────┼─────┼────────────┤
│                      │          │Head cabbages and       │
│                      │          │kohlrabi, Cauliflower   │
│                      │          │and broccoli, Brussels  │
│                      │          │sprouts ("buttons" only)│
│Brassica vegetables   │0.3   ppm │.                       │
│                      │          │The maximum tolerance   │
│                      │          │does not apply to       │
│                      │          │Brassica leafy          │
│                      │          │vegetables.             │
├───────────┼─────┼────────────┤
│                      │          │Whole commodity after   │
│                      │          │removing tops and       │
│                      │          │adhering soil. Potato   │
│Root and tuber        │0.1   ppm │must peel.              │
│vegetables            │          │The maximum tolerance   │
│                      │          │does not apply to       │
│                      │          │celeriac.               │
├───────────┼─────┼────────────┤
│                      │          │Dry onions and garlic   │
│                      │          │must removal of roots   │
│Bulb vegetables       │0.1   ppm │and adhering soil and   │
│                      │          │whatever parchment skin │
│                      │          │is easily detached.     │
├───────────┼─────┼────────────┤
│                      │          │Whole commodity after   │
│Fruiting vegetables   │0.1   ppm │removal of stems.       │
│                      │          │Sweet corn and fresh    │
│                      │          │corn without husk.      │
├───────────┼─────┼────────────┤
│Legume Vegetables     │0.2   ppm │Including edible pods.  │
├───────────┼─────┼────────────┤
│                      │          │Including edible crops  │
│Pulses                │0.2   ppm │harvested solely for dry│
│                      │          │seeds.                  │
├───────────┼─────┼────────────┤
│Peanuts               │0.2   ppm │                        │
├───────────┼─────┼────────────┤
│Berries and other     │0.2   ppm │                        │
│small fruits          │          │                        │
├───────────┼─────┼────────────┤
│Other vegetables and  │0.1   ppm │                        │
│fruits                │          │                        │
├───────────┼─────┼────────────┤
│Herbs and Spices      │0.3   ppm │                        │
│(fresh)               │          │                        │
└───────────┴─────┴────────────┘
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
